<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881111-0015 </DOCNO><HL> General Signal Contracts </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GSX MRN BBD.A </CO><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Signal Corp. said two of its units received contracts totaling $29 million for various transportation control equipment.    General Signal's General Railway Signal Corp. received a $14.4 million contract from the Chicago Transit Authority for railway switches. GRS also received a contract from the Chicago andamp; North Western Transportation Co. for an automatic vehicle identification system.    New York Air Brake, another unit of General Signal, received four contracts for braking systems totaling $14.2 million from Morrison-Knudsen Co., the New York City Transit Authority and Bombardier Inc.    General Signal manufactures instrumentation and control technology for semiconductors, industrial automation, energy management and rail transportation. </TEXT></DOC>